President Cyril Ramaphosa declared Nelson Mandela Bay Metro as a coronavirus hotspot during his address to the nation on Thursday. This is given to the number of new COVID-19 cases per day, the testing rate within the population, the percentage positivity rate within the population, the number of active cases, the number of hospital admissions and the number of deaths. In addition to the existing lockdown Level 1 regulations, the following additional restrictions came into effect in the metro from Friday midnight: